["'new_feature': 'health_risk_index'\n'detailed description': The health_risk_index is calculated by first computing the difference between systolic and diastolic blood pressure (sysbp - diabp), which represents pulse pressure. Then we add the square root of the glucose level and the logarithm of the total cholesterol level to the pulse pressure. Next, we consider the mean of the body mass index (bmi) for patients who are current smokers and have prevalent hypertension. Finally, we multiply this mean by the normalized value of age, and add it to the previous sum to form the final health_risk_index. This index captures the potential cardiovascular risk factors comprehensively.\n'brief description': A composite index reflecting cardiovascular risk factors based on blood pressure, glucose, cholesterol, BMI, smoking status, and age.\n'relevant': ['age', 'currentsmoker', 'prevalenthyp', 'totchol', 'sysbp', 'diabp', 'bmi', 'glucose']", "'new_feature': 'cholesterol_risk_factor'\n'detailed description': The cholesterol risk factor is calculated by taking the total cholesterol level (totchol) and adjusting it based on several considerations. It is increased by dividing the total cholesterol level by the mean systolic blood pressure (sysbp) of patients who are hypertensive (prevalenthyp = 1). Subsequently, it is reduced by multiplying the current cholesterol level with the mean Body Mass Index (bmi) of those who are not current smokers (currentsmoker = 0) but have diabetes (diabetes = 1). The final value is adjusted based on the glucose level with a factor of 0.5 only for individuals who are hypertensive. This feature aims to encapsulate the potential risk of coronary heart disease based on complex interactions between cholesterol, blood pressure, body mass index, smoking habits, and diabetes status.\n'brief description': Adjusted cholesterol level considering blood pressure, BMI, smoking, and diabetes status.\n'relevant': ['totchol', 'sysbp', 'bmi', 'currentsmoker', 'prevalenthyp', 'glucose', 'diabetes']", "'new_feature': 'risk_factor_score'\n'detailed description': A comprehensive risk factor score derived from multiple health indicators. The calculation includes: \n1. The standardized value of glucose, \n2. The average of bmi for females who are not current smokers, \n3. The product of prevalenthyp and diabetes for individuals older than 50, \n4. The mean value of systolic blood pressure for patients on blood pressure medications,\n5. The logarithm of the summation of totchol and age for those with no history of stroke.\nEach component is weighted by 0.7, 1.5, 1.2, 0.8, and 0.9 respectively, summed together, and divided by the average cigsperday for all individuals.\n'brief description': A weighted risk factor score calculated from key health indicators.\n'relevant': ['glucose', 'bmi', 'gender', 'currentsmoker', 'age', 'prevalenthyp', 'diabetes', 'bpmeds', 'sysbp', 'totchol', 'prevalentstroke', 'cigsperday']"]
