["'new_feature': 'advanced_health_score'\n'detailed description': This feature is calculated by taking the square root of the sum of systolic blood pressure (sysbp) and diastolic blood pressure (diabp), multiplied by the natural logarithm of total cholesterol (totchol), considering gender-specific adjustments. For males, further adjust the value by adding half of the BMI if the patient is a smoker but does not have diabetes. For females, subtract one-third of the glucose level if the patient is hypertensive and on blood pressure medication.\n'brief description': An advanced health score integrating blood pressure, cholesterol, gender-specific adjustments, and lifestyle factors.\n'relevant': ['gender', 'currentsmoker', 'diabetes', 'bpmeds', 'prevalenthyp', 'totchol', 'sysbp', 'diabp', 'bmi', 'glucose']", "'new_feature': 'stress_impact_index'\n'detailed description': This feature quantifies the impact of stress-related factors on cardiovascular health. It is calculated by multiplying the systolic blood pressure (sysbp) by the square root of the number of cigarettes smoked per day (cigsperday) for current smokers, divided by the body mass index (bmi) for individuals who are hypertensive, and then adjusted by adding the glucose level for diabetic patients. The result is then normalized across the dataset.\n'brief description': A composite index measuring cardiovascular stress factors related to smoking, blood pressure, and diabetes.\n'relevant': ['sysbp', 'cigsperday', 'bmi', 'prevalenthyp', 'currentsmoker', 'glucose', 'diabetes']", "'new_feature': 'adjusted_cardiovascular_risk'\n'detailed description': This feature calculates the cardiovascular risk by adjusting the systolic blood pressure and glucose levels. Specifically, it multiplies the systolic blood pressure of individuals who are smokers and have diabetes by 0.8, and adds it to the glucose level divided by 1.1 for individuals with hypertension but without prevalent stroke. This adjustment captures the compounded risk factors associated with smoking and diabetes on cardiovascular health.\n'brief description': A feature that adjusts cardiovascular risk using systolic blood pressure and glucose levels based on smoking, diabetes, and hypertension status.\n'relevant': ['currentsmoker', 'diabetes', 'prevalenthyp', 'prevalentstroke', 'sysbp', 'glucose']"]
