["'new_feature': 'comprehensive_cardio_health_index'\n'detailed description': Calculate the weighted sum of systolic and diastolic blood pressure, total cholesterol, and BMI. Adjust these values by multiplying systolic blood pressure by 1.5 if the individual is hypertensive, and multiply total cholesterol by 0.8 if the individual is diabetic. Add the product of glucose level and age, adjusted by dividing age by 10. Integrate heart rate by dividing it by 2 if the individual is a current smoker. Finally, normalize this sum by the logarithm of 1 plus the average heart rate across all individuals.\n'brief description': A high-order compound metric integrating key cardiovascular indicators, adjusted for hypertension, diabetes, and smoking status, normalized by average heart rate.\n'relevant': [age, currentsmoker, bpm, prevalenthyp, diabetes, totchol, sysbp, diabp, bmi, heartrate, glucose]", "'new_feature': 'lifestyle_impact_score'\n'detailed description': This feature evaluates the impact of lifestyle factors such as smoking, diabetes, and hypertension on the overall health risks. It is calculated as the sum of systolic blood pressure (sysbp), diastolic blood pressure (diabp), cholesterol level (totchol), and glucose level, adjusted by adding a weighted factor for smoking status. The feature is further adjusted by reducing the value for individuals who are not on blood pressure medication, and adding an adjustment for those who have diabetes.\n'brief description': Lifestyle Impact Score assesses the compounded effect of lifestyle and chronic health conditions on cardiovascular risk.\n'relevant': [gender, currentsmoker, bpmeds, diabetes, totchol, sysbp, diabp, glucose, cholesterol_risk_factor, cardio_metabolic_factor, advanced_health_score]", "'new_feature': 'lifestyle_adjusted_risk_score'\n'detailed description': This feature combines lifestyle factors such as smoking and BMI with medical conditions including hypertension and diabetes to assess their collective impact on