["'new_feature': 'holistic_wellness_index',\n'detailed description': The holistic wellness index is calculated by combining multiple health indicators and lifestyle factors. It includes the average BMI of individuals who are not prevalent stroke patients, adjusted by their systolic and diastolic blood pressure levels. This is further refined by subtracting the glucose levels from the total cholesterol, and dividing by the heart rate. The result is multiplied by a factor of 1.5 for current smokers who smoke more than 10 cigarettes per day, and adjusted for gender, doubling the value for males.\n'brief description': An index representing overall wellness, combining key health and lifestyle factors, with specific adjustments for smoking habits and gender.\n'relevant': [gender, currentsmoker, cigsperday, prevalentstroke, totchol, sysbp, diabp, bmi, heartrate, glucose]", "'new_feature': 'cardiovascular_stability_index'\n'detailed description': The Cardiovascular Stability Index (CSI) is calculated by combining the normalized systolic and diastolic blood pressure levels, adjusted for age, BMI, presence of diabetes, and smoking status. It emphasizes blood pressure consistency relative to personal health conditions associated with cardiovascular risk.\n'brief description': This index captures the stability of cardiovascular metrics in relation to personal health modifiers.\n'relevant': ['sysbp', 'diabp', 'age', 'bmi', 'diabetes', 'currentsmoker']", "'new_feature': 'integrated_health_risk_index'\n'detailed description': This feature combines standardized values of systolic blood pressure and total cholesterol levels, adjusted by diabetes status, age, and smoking habits. It computes the weighted sum of systolic blood pressure normalized by age and diabetes status, total cholesterol normalized by the mean value of glucose, and the number of cigarettes smoked per day. The weights applied are 0.75 for systolic blood pressure, 0.5 for total cholesterol, and 0.25 for smoking impact. This integrated approach provides a nuanced assessment of health risk.\n'brief description': An index integrating blood pressure, cholesterol, age, smoking effects, and diabetes status to assess health risks.\n'relevant': [gender, age, currentsmoker, cigsperday, diabetes, totchol, sysbp, glucose]"]
